Application subsystem for plotting tide calendars with gnuplot  

Development Environment: 
(ntcm.bom.gov.au) /home/james/bin/utilities/tidecalendars2

Porting script:
(ntcm.bom.gov.au) /home/james/bin/utilities/tidecalendars2/dev2ops.scr

Manual:
Edit word document (/home/james/bin/utilities/tidecalendars2/doc) and make pdf
Make examples with cookbook.ksh then concatentate ps and ps2pdf
Use adobe acrobat to insert/replace examples into manual

Operational Environment:
/g/ns/ntc/op/dm/bin/tidecalendars2
Shared storage for use by all virtual servers

NOTE:
Do not edit the operational environment unless you really need to.
Make changes in the development environment, and then port across

Main executable:
(Symbolic link) /g/ns/ntc/op/dm/bin/tide_calendar2

For help:
tide_calendar2 -h

James Chittleborough  Sep 2020 (tide_calendar)

